def calculoDescriptores(listaSMILES, listaDescriptores):
    rdkit_featurizer = dc.feat.RDKitDescriptors(descriptors = listaDescriptores)
    features = rdkit_featurizer(listaSMILES)
    return features

def qed_logP_tox21(num_atomos, lista_atomos):
    tasks, datasets, transformers = dc.molnet.load_tox21() #Llamamos al objeto molnet.load_dataset dentro de la librera DeepChem
    df_tox21 = pd.DataFrame(data={'smiles': datasets[0].ids})
    smiles = df_tox21['smiles'].values
    feat = dc.feat.MolGanFeaturizer(max_atom_count=num_atomos, atom_labels=lista_atomos)
    filtered_smiles = [x for x in smiles if Chem.MolFromSmiles(x).GetNumAtoms() < 18]
    features = feat.featurize(filtered_smiles)
    moleculas_rdkit = list(filter(lambda x: x is not None, feat.defeaturize(features)))
    moleculas_smiles = [Chem.MolToSmiles(m) for m in moleculas_rdkit]
    propiedades = calculoDescriptores(moleculas_smiles, ["ExactMolWt", "MolLogP", "qed"])
    peso_data, logP_data, qed_data = zip(*propiedades)
    return peso_data, logP_data, qed_data

def qed_logP_qm9():
    tasks, datasets, transformers = dc.molnet.load_qm9() #Llamamos al objeto molnet.load_dataset dentro de la librera DeepChem
    df_qm9 = pd.DataFrame(data={'smiles': datasets[0].ids})
    df_qm9_sample_5 = df_qm9.sample(5000, random_state = 123)
    smiles_qm9 = df_qm9_sample_5["smiles"].values
    propiedades = calculoDescriptores(smiles_qm9, ["ExactMolWt", "MolLogP", "qed"])
    peso_data, logP_data, qed_data = zip(*propiedades)
    return peso_data, logP_data, qed_data
